// Man page for diff
manDiff="DIFF(1)                          X Shell Manual                          DIFF(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    diff - Compare files or directories
<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>diff</b> AFILE BFILE
    <b>diff</b> AFILE BFILE > output.txt
    <b>diff</b> AFILE BFILE >> output.txt
<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    Compare two files or directories and display lines or files that differ.
    If the files or directories are identical, no output is produced. Supports
    output redirection with > (overwrite), >> (append), and --post flags.

    *** Redirect output is never printed to the tty ***
<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <color=#e4ff34># Compare Files</color>
    <b>diff file1.txt file2.txt</b>
    Show differences between two files

    <color=#e4ff34># Save Differences</color>
    <b>diff file1.txt file2.txt > changes.txt</b>
    Save differences to file

    <b>diff dir1 dir2</b>
    Compare two directories
<b>SEE ALSO</b>
    <b>grep</b>, <b>cat</b>"